1
00:00:06,666 --> 00:00:10,750
[tense rock music playing]

2
00:00:14,625 --> 00:00:16,958
Go on. Come at me.

3
00:00:17,041 --> 00:00:18,708
You piece of shit.

4
00:00:19,416 --> 00:00:22,416
Bastard. You really wanna die, do you?

5
00:00:23,333 --> 00:00:25,791
[Shimura] <i>I can tell</i>
<i>he's overcome with rage.</i>

6
00:00:27,125 --> 00:00:28,625
<i>This is…</i>

7
00:00:29,291 --> 00:00:30,416
[gasps]

8
00:00:36,208 --> 00:00:37,208
[clicks]

9
00:00:37,291 --> 00:00:41,291
[TOU-KEI] <i>Rule number one.</i>
<i>Don't lose your cool.</i>

10
00:00:42,541 --> 00:00:46,291
<i>It's easy to defeat</i>
<i>someone who's lost their cool.</i>

11
00:00:47,166 --> 00:00:49,833
<i>If you can't keep yourself under control,</i>

12
00:00:49,916 --> 00:00:54,875
<i>then you're using your emotions,</i>
<i>not your fists.</i>

13
00:00:55,375 --> 00:00:59,666
<i>In other words, if you can get</i>
<i>your opponent to lose his cool,</i>

14
00:01:00,166 --> 00:01:03,208
<i>then you gain you a significant advantage.</i>

15
00:01:08,416 --> 00:01:10,333
- [Hamaken grunts]
- [students gasp]

16
00:01:11,208 --> 00:01:12,250
[Shimura] <i>I dodged.</i>

17
00:01:12,958 --> 00:01:16,750
<i>Just maybe…</i>
<i>that chicken guy is the real deal.</i>

18
00:01:16,833 --> 00:01:18,708
<i>Can his videos actually make me stronger?</i>

19
00:01:18,791 --> 00:01:20,416
Quit dodging! Agh!

20
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:23,958
[Shimura] <i>Here it comes again.</i>
<i>If I'm gonna get hit, I might as well try…</i>

21
00:01:24,041 --> 00:01:26,166
[TOU-KEI] <i>A punch is at its most powerful</i>

22
00:01:26,250 --> 00:01:28,541
<i>when the arm is fully extended.</i>

23
00:01:28,625 --> 00:01:32,708
<i>So if you can take the hit before</i>
<i>your opponent fully extends his arm,</i>

24
00:01:34,166 --> 00:01:36,166
<i>it won't hurt so much.</i>

25
00:01:36,250 --> 00:01:40,166
<i>We'll call it</i>
<i>the "how to get hit without pain" method.</i>

26
00:01:40,250 --> 00:01:41,833
[Shimura] <i>He's right.</i>

27
00:01:41,916 --> 00:01:44,083
<i>It doesn't… hurt!</i>

28
00:01:44,166 --> 00:01:47,541
- What the hell is he doing?
- [tense electronic music playing]

29
00:01:47,625 --> 00:01:49,375
[Shimura] <i>That chicken guy was right.</i>

30
00:01:50,333 --> 00:01:51,583
<i>Just who the hell is he?</i>

31
00:01:52,083 --> 00:01:53,125
[Hamaken roars]

32
00:01:53,625 --> 00:01:56,375
[music intensifies]

33
00:01:56,458 --> 00:01:58,666
[Shimura] <i>I can do this. I can win!</i>

34
00:01:59,166 --> 00:02:02,000
[panting]

35
00:02:04,208 --> 00:02:05,125
[Shimura] <i>Wait!</i>

36
00:02:05,208 --> 00:02:07,208
- [music stops]
<i>- What comes after this?</i>

37
00:02:08,625 --> 00:02:09,875
<i>Hold on.</i>

38
00:02:09,958 --> 00:02:12,375
<i>- What am I supposed to do next?</i>
- [tense music playing]

39
00:02:12,458 --> 00:02:13,791
[light switch clicks]

40
00:02:13,875 --> 00:02:16,000
[Shimura] <i>Wait! I need you to tell me--</i>

41
00:02:16,083 --> 00:02:17,000
[Hamaken roars]

42
00:02:17,458 --> 00:02:19,416
[gagging, straining]

43
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:20,333
Shimura…

44
00:02:24,041 --> 00:02:26,250
You've got some nerve, haven't you?

45
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:27,208
<i>Oh shit.</i>

46
00:02:27,291 --> 00:02:28,125
[squeaks]

47
00:02:28,625 --> 00:02:30,583
<i>I should've watched the next video too.</i>

48
00:02:31,083 --> 00:02:32,250
[groaning]

49
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:34,833
- [Hamaken] You're fucking dead--
- [girl] Stop right there!

50
00:02:34,916 --> 00:02:38,125
[music fades]

51
00:02:38,208 --> 00:02:40,125
I'm streaming the both of you.

52
00:02:41,791 --> 00:02:44,375
So, are you going to continue doing this?

53
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:50,958
[Hamaken] You bastards.

54
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:53,333
You'll pay for this.

55
00:03:07,458 --> 00:03:09,375
How long has it been rolling for?

56
00:03:11,041 --> 00:03:12,041
It never went live.

57
00:03:12,125 --> 00:03:14,000
- What?!
- I was bluffing.

58
00:03:20,541 --> 00:03:23,250
Thank you for saving me.

59
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:26,666
- Don't mention it.
- Your name is?

60
00:03:28,250 --> 00:03:30,083
Yashio Aki. I'm a first-year.

61
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,125
Oh. Younger than us.

62
00:03:32,208 --> 00:03:34,833
I lived abroad for quite some time.

63
00:03:35,541 --> 00:03:37,708
So, I'm kind of new around here.

64
00:03:38,208 --> 00:03:39,666
I see. That's nice.

65
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:41,875
You should just thank her
for saving your ass.

66
00:03:43,291 --> 00:03:44,750
So, you're Aki.

67
00:03:44,833 --> 00:03:46,125
That's a nice name.

68
00:03:47,125 --> 00:03:50,291
Agh! You know,
if you'd only held out for longer,

69
00:03:50,375 --> 00:03:52,833
the donations were starting to come in.

70
00:03:53,458 --> 00:03:55,708
How much money did we make?

71
00:03:57,750 --> 00:03:59,166
25,000.

72
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:01,750
Oh, that's all?

73
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:07,791
Well, you would've wasted your time
trying to hang out any longer.

74
00:04:08,666 --> 00:04:10,958
I think that could've been the end of you.

75
00:04:11,625 --> 00:04:12,791
Yes. You're right, there.

76
00:04:12,875 --> 00:04:14,541
So, I'm curious.

77
00:04:14,625 --> 00:04:17,333
Who edits the videos
after the streaming's over?

78
00:04:17,791 --> 00:04:19,625
Uh… I do.

79
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:23,000
- Oh, you like my editing?
- It's mediocre.

80
00:04:23,083 --> 00:04:24,208
Oh.

81
00:04:24,291 --> 00:04:26,541
You'll never get more viewers like this.

82
00:04:26,625 --> 00:04:30,000
And the fewer the viewers,
then the fewer the donations.

83
00:04:30,583 --> 00:04:33,625
But… what can we do about that?

84
00:04:34,333 --> 00:04:35,166
[Aki] Hmm.

85
00:04:36,208 --> 00:04:37,875
I'm pretty good at editing, you know?

86
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:39,625
- Oh?
- Huh?

87
00:04:39,708 --> 00:04:41,750
[Toru laughs]

88
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,333
Why don't you let me assist you?

89
00:04:47,541 --> 00:04:49,625
[upbeat electronic music playing]

90
00:04:50,916 --> 00:04:51,875
- Hey.
- Yeah?

91
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:54,125
- Is this girl really gonna be our editor?
- Why not?

92
00:04:54,208 --> 00:04:56,625
- We could use a female perspective.
- Leave it to me.

93
00:04:56,708 --> 00:04:58,250
I'll get you more subscribers.

94
00:04:58,333 --> 00:05:01,375
You see? She's going to get us
a lot more subscribers!

95
00:05:01,458 --> 00:05:04,250
And we need a name. What though?

96
00:05:04,333 --> 00:05:06,708
True. Right now it's
still "Kanegon TV" now.

97
00:05:06,791 --> 00:05:09,000
Maybe Aki can come up with a new name.

98
00:05:09,083 --> 00:05:11,625
Girls are good
at that sort of thing, aren't you?

99
00:05:11,708 --> 00:05:13,750
I've already thought of one.

100
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:15,250
Hey, for real?

101
00:05:17,666 --> 00:05:20,041
What about "Viral Hit"?

102
00:05:20,625 --> 00:05:23,541
- What?
- "Viral Hit"?

103
00:05:23,625 --> 00:05:24,750
[jaunty music playing]

104
00:05:24,833 --> 00:05:26,958
HOW_TO_FIGHT

105
00:05:27,041 --> 00:05:28,708
Aki, that's a little--

106
00:05:28,791 --> 00:05:30,458
You don't like it, I'll quit then.

107
00:05:31,541 --> 00:05:32,791
Wait a second.

108
00:05:32,875 --> 00:05:36,083
Actually, it's quite original.
Oh, it's good!

109
00:05:36,166 --> 00:05:37,333
You like it too?

110
00:05:37,416 --> 00:05:39,875
- Yeah.
- It's decided then.

111
00:05:39,958 --> 00:05:43,875
Today's we become known as <i>Viral Hit</i>!

112
00:05:43,958 --> 00:05:45,791
You're gonna be so busy! Huh? Huh?

113
00:05:45,875 --> 00:05:48,208
You won't have time to fry potatoes!

114
00:05:48,291 --> 00:05:50,333
- Sure.
- [Aki chuckles]

115
00:05:54,083 --> 00:05:55,166
AMERICAN HOUSE DINER

116
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:56,625
[TOU-KEI] <i>Let's enjoy!</i>

117
00:05:56,708 --> 00:06:01,000
<i>One, two, three, four,</i>
<i>five, and six, seven, eight.</i>

118
00:06:01,083 --> 00:06:04,583
<i>One, two, three, four, five, six.</i>
<i>Raise your legs high!</i>

119
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:08,750
<i>Tighten your abs. Now exhale. One…</i>

120
00:06:08,833 --> 00:06:10,166
I'm beat.

121
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:12,375
[panting]

122
00:06:14,375 --> 00:06:17,291
Will I really get stronger doing this?

123
00:06:17,875 --> 00:06:19,333
[continues panting]

124
00:06:20,333 --> 00:06:23,708
<i>Who was it that sent me this video</i>
<i>in the first place?</i>

125
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,916
Hey, Shimura, your break's almost over.

126
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,000
- Asamiya-san.
<i>- </i>[TOU-KEI] <i>One, two, three…</i>

127
00:06:29,083 --> 00:06:31,541
- Okay then. Thank you.
- <i>Four, five, six, seven, eight!</i>

128
00:06:31,625 --> 00:06:34,583
<i>- One, two, three, four, five, six, seven…</i>
- Hey, I can hear something.

129
00:06:34,666 --> 00:06:36,416
- What?
<i>- Moving on to heel jacks now!</i>

130
00:06:36,500 --> 00:06:39,333
<i>- One, two, three…</i>
- Oh. Probably just your imagination.

131
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:41,458
- Ah. Okay.
- <i>One, two…</i>

132
00:06:41,541 --> 00:06:44,083
The manager wants to talk to you
about your schedule.

133
00:06:44,166 --> 00:06:47,000
Oh. I had a hunch he would. Thank you.

134
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:49,291
[breathing heavily]

135
00:06:54,125 --> 00:06:56,375
[Karakida] I can't just take you
out of the schedule.

136
00:06:56,458 --> 00:06:58,958
If you don't give me any notice,
it's gonna be hard.

137
00:06:59,041 --> 00:07:01,125
So sorry. I know this is late notice.

138
00:07:01,208 --> 00:07:03,666
Shimura, you're here
almost every single day.

139
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:04,791
Yeah…

140
00:07:06,791 --> 00:07:10,000
[Karakida groans] How about this?
Jessica could cover Ryan.

141
00:07:10,083 --> 00:07:13,666
- Or… ugh, I don't know--
- [Kaho] I have an idea.

142
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:18,541
What if the rest of us took turns
on the days Shimura can't come in yet?

143
00:07:18,625 --> 00:07:19,458
Huh.

144
00:07:19,541 --> 00:07:22,333
We could set up a group chat
for the part-timers.

145
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:25,583
[man] Yeah, sounds like a good idea.
Let's do it.

146
00:07:25,666 --> 00:07:27,083
- [Kaho] Okay.
- [man] Works for me.

147
00:07:27,166 --> 00:07:28,125
[woman] Sure, go ahead.

148
00:07:28,208 --> 00:07:29,041
KAHO ASAMIYA

149
00:07:29,125 --> 00:07:31,750
[Toru] You just exchanged line accounts,
that's all.

150
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:33,000
You can say what you want.

151
00:07:33,083 --> 00:07:38,208
But this phone is now a bridge
and it connects us together! [squeals]

152
00:07:39,291 --> 00:07:40,916
[Kaho] <i>Thanks for connecting with me.</i>

153
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,083
Even her sticker… it's gorgeous!

154
00:07:44,166 --> 00:07:45,291
Oh!

155
00:07:45,375 --> 00:07:48,375
Hey! Wait! You're that famous streamer!

156
00:07:48,458 --> 00:07:51,416
- Oh, do you know me?
- Well, of course I do!

157
00:07:51,500 --> 00:07:53,916
- Whoa! It's really you!
- Hey, I'm his producer, you know.

158
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,291
Who are these guys anyway?

159
00:07:56,375 --> 00:07:57,875
Celebrities!

160
00:07:57,958 --> 00:07:59,833
[screaming]

161
00:07:59,916 --> 00:08:01,625
- [both laughing]
- [woman] Hey, hey, hey!

162
00:08:01,708 --> 00:08:04,458
- This is our lucky day!
- Why don't we go talk over there?

163
00:08:04,541 --> 00:08:06,291
- Yeah, okay. Okay.
- [woman squealing]

164
00:08:06,375 --> 00:08:07,791
- Let's go!
- Can I shake your hand?

165
00:08:07,875 --> 00:08:08,708
Sure. Of course.

166
00:08:08,791 --> 00:08:10,375
- Whoa!
- Yeah, go ahead.

167
00:08:10,458 --> 00:08:12,666
- You're so good-looking.
- You're so much cooler in person!

168
00:08:13,583 --> 00:08:15,333
And… jump.

169
00:08:15,416 --> 00:08:19,458
- Jump, jump, jump, jump! [giggles]
- [coins jangling]

170
00:08:19,541 --> 00:08:22,083
Hey! You're still hiding money in there!

171
00:08:22,666 --> 00:08:24,833
[Shimura] <i>I suspected</i>
<i>it would lead to this.</i>

172
00:08:24,916 --> 00:08:26,250
[man] It's a big light on.

173
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:29,791
Hey! These guys don't have
much cash at all.

174
00:08:29,875 --> 00:08:32,333
What?! I thought you guys were loaded.

175
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:34,166
No. This is so lame.

176
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:35,708
Hey.

177
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:37,875
This here is mine now.

178
00:08:37,958 --> 00:08:39,916
No! That's my bridge to Asamiya!

179
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,291
- Shut the hell up!
- [groaning]

180
00:08:41,375 --> 00:08:43,750
Touch me again, kid,
and you are going down.

181
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:47,333
- Ken, you're so brutal! I just love you.
- You think so?

182
00:08:47,416 --> 00:08:48,875
- [Shimura] Hey! Wait!
- I love you too.

183
00:08:48,958 --> 00:08:51,333
- [woman] I'm starving. Can we eat now?
- [Ken] Yeah, let's go.

184
00:08:51,416 --> 00:08:54,791
Kanegon, we've got to notify the police
and get my phone back!

185
00:08:54,875 --> 00:08:56,666
Huh? Notify the police?

186
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:58,041
Are you kidding?!

187
00:08:58,625 --> 00:08:59,583
Huh?

188
00:08:59,666 --> 00:09:02,291
Look! All the fans going wild.

189
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:03,916
[Shimura] Were you streaming?

190
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:06,125
Yeah, of course I was.

191
00:09:08,125 --> 00:09:09,458
Can't you hear it?

192
00:09:09,541 --> 00:09:12,000
I can hear the jingle
of cash hitting our account.

193
00:09:13,791 --> 00:09:16,416
That means
I get beaten up again, doesn't it?

194
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:18,500
So you want out?

195
00:09:19,708 --> 00:09:22,791
Fine. I get it.
We'll go talk to the police.

196
00:09:22,875 --> 00:09:24,125
[Shimura] The police.

197
00:09:29,208 --> 00:09:31,000
No way.  We can't.

198
00:09:35,583 --> 00:09:39,125
<i>Viral Hit's </i>live stream is starting now!

199
00:09:39,208 --> 00:09:40,958
PROB GONNA MAKE A DONATION

200
00:09:41,041 --> 00:09:42,833
I'VE BEEN WAITING FOR THIS!

201
00:09:42,916 --> 00:09:44,583
THIS IS GONNA BE EPIC!

202
00:09:44,666 --> 00:09:46,166
I'M DONATING, TOO!

203
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:48,250
[suspenseful music playing]

204
00:09:53,333 --> 00:09:58,833
VIRAL HIT

205
00:09:58,916 --> 00:10:01,000
- [Ken] What? You want your phone back?
- [music fades]

206
00:10:01,083 --> 00:10:02,791
That's right. Please give it back.

207
00:10:02,875 --> 00:10:05,291
[woman] Ken, they're
here filming us now, you know?

208
00:10:05,375 --> 00:10:08,041
Oh, yeah? Now I'll be famous, right?

209
00:10:08,125 --> 00:10:09,166
- Yeah!
- Hey.

210
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:11,083
I really think
you should stop filming me, okay?

211
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:12,583
[Toru] Don't worry, I will.

212
00:10:13,083 --> 00:10:15,166
Hey! What did you want from me?

213
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:18,250
Like I said, I want my phone back.

214
00:10:18,333 --> 00:10:19,666
What if I say no?

215
00:10:20,500 --> 00:10:21,833
If you refuse,

216
00:10:22,458 --> 00:10:24,083
you leave me no choice.

217
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:26,791
[both laughing]

218
00:10:26,875 --> 00:10:28,000
Are you for real, now?

219
00:10:28,083 --> 00:10:30,666
God damn, kid. Just smack him, Ken.

220
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:33,041
- Well, let's see, huh?
- [woman squealing]

221
00:10:33,125 --> 00:10:35,000
Everybody watching, check me out now,

222
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:37,666
and make him know for sure
that I is the man!

223
00:10:37,750 --> 00:10:39,541
- [woman] Whoo! Go, Ken!
- [crowd cheering]

224
00:10:39,625 --> 00:10:43,125
[Shimura] <i>This is my chance</i>
<i>to try out what I've learned.</i>

225
00:10:43,208 --> 00:10:47,250
[TOU-KEI] <i>First, identify your opponent's</i>
<i>dominant hand.</i>

226
00:10:47,333 --> 00:10:49,500
<i>If your opponent is an amateur fighter,</i>

227
00:10:49,583 --> 00:10:53,041
<i>there's a high chancel they'll use</i>
<i>their dominant hand to strike.</i>

228
00:10:53,125 --> 00:10:54,708
<i>His dominant hand is…</i>

229
00:10:54,791 --> 00:10:57,041
- No! That's my bridge to Asamiya!
- Shut the hell up!

230
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:58,750
[Shimura] <i>He's right-handed.</i>

231
00:10:58,833 --> 00:11:00,875
[TOU-KEI] <i>If your opponent is</i>
<i>right-handed,</i>

232
00:11:00,958 --> 00:11:02,958
<i>then stand on their left side</i>

233
00:11:03,041 --> 00:11:05,541
<i>so they're likely to swing</i>
<i>using their right hand.</i>

234
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:09,750
<i>You see, now you force them</i>
<i>to swing at you using their right hand.</i>

235
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,416
You're looking scared! Ready to have fun?

236
00:11:11,500 --> 00:11:14,416
[TOU-KEI] <i>Not sure</i>
<i>when to dodge the punch?</i>

237
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:15,875
<i>It's simple.</i>

238
00:11:15,958 --> 00:11:18,666
<i>People who lack training in martial arts </i>

239
00:11:18,750 --> 00:11:22,583
<i>tend to move their shoulders very wide</i>
<i>when they swing at you.</i>

240
00:11:22,666 --> 00:11:24,583
[Ken roars]

241
00:11:25,625 --> 00:11:26,583
[TOU-KEI] Now!

242
00:11:26,666 --> 00:11:27,833
- [crowd gasping]
- [Ken grunts]

243
00:11:27,916 --> 00:11:29,875
- [rock music playing]
- You little rat!

244
00:11:29,958 --> 00:11:31,875
[woman] Come on, Ken! Get him!

245
00:11:31,958 --> 00:11:33,291
- [Ken grunts]
- [clattering]

246
00:11:33,375 --> 00:11:34,666
You bastard!

247
00:11:36,750 --> 00:11:38,041
[Ken grunts]

248
00:11:38,125 --> 00:11:39,125
HE'S DANCING LOL

249
00:11:39,208 --> 00:11:40,500
CHICKEN DANCE LOL

250
00:11:41,708 --> 00:11:43,500
[Ken] <i>What's that weird-ass move?</i>

251
00:11:44,166 --> 00:11:45,833
[Aki] <i>Weaving. That's basic technique.</i>

252
00:11:45,916 --> 00:11:47,916
LET'S GO SHIMURA! LMAO

253
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:51,458
[TOU-KEI] <i>Well done! You're doing well.</i>

254
00:11:51,541 --> 00:11:52,916
God damn it! Stop moving!

255
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,041
- [woman] Go, Ken! Go! Get him!
- [Ken grunting]

256
00:11:55,125 --> 00:11:58,208
<i>You'll find it's very hard</i>
<i>for the average person</i>

257
00:11:58,291 --> 00:12:00,166
<i>to land a punch on a moving target.</i>

258
00:12:01,416 --> 00:12:03,750
- [crowd clamoring]
- [Shimura] <i>That one worked too.</i>

259
00:12:03,833 --> 00:12:04,791
Aerobics?

260
00:12:04,875 --> 00:12:07,583
[TOU-KEI] <i>Aerobics will teach you</i>
<i>how to move your body.</i>

261
00:12:08,125 --> 00:12:10,500
<i>And you will learn about rhythm too.</i>

262
00:12:10,583 --> 00:12:12,125
- [woman] Yes, Ken!
- [Ken] Stop moving!

263
00:12:12,208 --> 00:12:13,291
Wait! Wait! Wait!

264
00:12:13,375 --> 00:12:14,291
[screaming]

265
00:12:14,375 --> 00:12:17,333
[fighters grunting]

266
00:12:18,291 --> 00:12:20,500
[Ken] Come back here, you little shit!

267
00:12:22,041 --> 00:12:23,958
[Ken snarling]

268
00:12:24,041 --> 00:12:25,583
[grunting]

269
00:12:25,666 --> 00:12:26,625
Get outta my way!

270
00:12:26,708 --> 00:12:27,583
[grunts]

271
00:12:29,375 --> 00:12:31,666
[Shimura] <i>It… didn't hurt.</i>

272
00:12:33,708 --> 00:12:36,875
[TOU-KEI] <i>Fighting isn't</i>
<i>so intimidating anymore, is it?</i>

273
00:12:37,583 --> 00:12:40,375
<i>So now, let's enjoy!</i>

274
00:12:40,458 --> 00:12:43,250
- Now, Ken!
- Now say good night, kid! [grunts]

275
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:47,458
- [grunting]
- [woman screaming]

276
00:12:52,041 --> 00:12:53,875
[Shimura panting]

277
00:12:53,958 --> 00:12:56,375
- [Ken continues grunting]
- [woman screaming]

278
00:12:56,458 --> 00:12:57,333
Wait, what?

279
00:12:57,416 --> 00:12:59,958
[Toru] Move! Move!
Let me through! Move! Move!

280
00:13:00,041 --> 00:13:02,833
- Ken, what's happening?
- And now you're gonna die!

281
00:13:02,916 --> 00:13:05,416
[Shimura] <i>Oh crap! I can't move an inch!</i>

282
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,416
Dumbass!

283
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,791
[Shimura] <i>"How to get hit without pain"!</i>

284
00:13:09,875 --> 00:13:10,875
[Ken grunts]

285
00:13:12,458 --> 00:13:13,458
- Huh?
- [woman] Ken?

286
00:13:13,541 --> 00:13:14,958
[music subsides]

287
00:13:15,041 --> 00:13:18,458
Give me back… my phone.

288
00:13:18,541 --> 00:13:21,125
[snarling]

289
00:13:21,208 --> 00:13:22,750
[suspenseful music playing]

290
00:13:22,833 --> 00:13:24,125
I WANNA LEARN THIS

291
00:13:24,208 --> 00:13:25,750
REVENGE OF THE UNDERDOG!

292
00:13:26,333 --> 00:13:27,333
[Ken grunts]

293
00:13:28,125 --> 00:13:30,166
- [crowd clamoring]
- [bottle shatters]

294
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:32,000
- [glass shattering]
- [Ken straining]

295
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:33,916
[Ken grunting, yelling]

296
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:35,416
[woman] <i>You got it, Ken!</i>

297
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:37,791
DO YOU HAVE A PLATE IN YOUR FOREHEAD?

298
00:13:37,875 --> 00:13:39,291
[grunting]

299
00:13:39,375 --> 00:13:40,750
HE'S TAKING ALL THE HITS

300
00:13:40,833 --> 00:13:42,333
CAN'T BEAT A REAL THUG

301
00:13:45,208 --> 00:13:47,833
[Aki] Not so sure about that.
Look at that thug's fist.

302
00:13:47,916 --> 00:13:49,083
[crowd clamoring] Hey!

303
00:13:49,166 --> 00:13:51,708
- [Ken groans] Oh!
- [woman] What? Huh? Huh? Oh!

304
00:13:51,791 --> 00:13:53,875
- [Ken yells in pain]
- [woman] Ken, are you okay?

305
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:55,541
Yeah, yeah. I'm good.

306
00:13:55,625 --> 00:13:57,708
- [Ken] <i>This sucks!</i>
- [woman] <i>Ken, you poor thing!</i>

307
00:13:57,791 --> 00:14:00,208
[Aki] <i>He doesn't realize it</i>
<i>because of the adrenaline,</i>

308
00:14:00,291 --> 00:14:01,833
<i>but his fist is all banged up.</i>

309
00:14:01,916 --> 00:14:02,833
[woman whimpering]

310
00:14:02,916 --> 00:14:04,708
Shit! [snarling]

311
00:14:04,791 --> 00:14:06,750
Okay. Take it then!

312
00:14:06,833 --> 00:14:08,125
[crowd] Whoa!

313
00:14:08,208 --> 00:14:09,083
[man laughs]

314
00:14:09,166 --> 00:14:12,041
Fine. You're all gonna see me again.

315
00:14:12,125 --> 00:14:13,708
- Come on!
- Assholes!

316
00:14:13,791 --> 00:14:14,833
[crowd cheering]

317
00:14:14,916 --> 00:14:16,333
<i>Asamiya!</i>

318
00:14:16,416 --> 00:14:18,458
You did it, Shimura!

319
00:14:18,541 --> 00:14:21,125
Now, a word
for all the viewers who donated.

320
00:14:21,708 --> 00:14:23,750
Don't miss our next performance, okay?

321
00:14:23,833 --> 00:14:26,125
<i>That's all from </i>Viral Hit.

322
00:14:26,208 --> 00:14:30,000
<i>Oh, I forgot to say, please keep</i>
<i>the donations coming! </i>[laughs]

323
00:14:30,541 --> 00:14:33,166
[Toru] <i>Hey, are you in pain?</i>
<i>You got beaten up there.</i>

324
00:14:33,250 --> 00:14:34,541
<i>Oh, no.</i>

325
00:14:34,625 --> 00:14:36,833
<i>Uh, uh, well, a little. Yeah.</i>

326
00:14:36,916 --> 00:14:38,041
SO IT DOES HURT LOL

327
00:14:38,125 --> 00:14:40,208
SHIMURA, HERO OF BULLIED KIDS!

328
00:14:40,291 --> 00:14:41,958
49,917 VIEWERS WATCHING NOW

329
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:46,583
<i>- </i>[Toru] <i>Hey, don't forget to subscribe!</i>
<i>- </i>[Shimura] <i>And, uh, please donate!</i>

330
00:14:46,666 --> 00:14:48,333
[Toru] <i>Yeah, keep the donations coming!</i>

331
00:14:48,416 --> 00:14:49,583
[girl] <i>You were so great!</i>

332
00:14:49,666 --> 00:14:50,875
[Toru] <i>Thank you!</i>

333
00:14:52,083 --> 00:14:53,416
<i>- You're so cute.</i>
<i>- Thank you.</i>

334
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:55,833
<i>- Hi!</i>
<i>- </i>[Shimura] <i>Uh, oh, okay.</i>

335
00:14:55,916 --> 00:14:59,166
[Shimura] <i>Please subscribe to our channel,</i>
<i>um, and make donations.</i>

336
00:15:03,708 --> 00:15:04,708
[music fades]

337
00:15:08,583 --> 00:15:10,750
[fast-forward clicking]

338
00:15:15,208 --> 00:15:19,083
[Shimura] <i>Currently, we have five videos</i>
<i>on our </i>Viral Hit <i>channel.</i>

339
00:15:19,166 --> 00:15:22,500
<i>And we've reached</i>
<i>more than five million views in total.</i>

340
00:15:22,583 --> 00:15:23,416
<i>And…</i>

341
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,166
[jaunty music playing]

342
00:15:25,250 --> 00:15:28,041
- [Toru] All right! We did it!
- Yay!

343
00:15:28,125 --> 00:15:30,875
[Shimura] <i>Now we have our first payout.</i>

344
00:15:30,958 --> 00:15:32,583
<i>This is more than my job pays.</i>

345
00:15:33,166 --> 00:15:35,958
[Toru] Well, we're in the money now,
aren't we, huh?!

346
00:15:37,625 --> 00:15:39,833
How should we divide it?

347
00:15:40,458 --> 00:15:42,291
- I'm okay. I don't care.
- You sure?

348
00:15:42,375 --> 00:15:43,750
It's not okay.

349
00:15:43,833 --> 00:15:46,166
You don't need
to be so considerate like that.

350
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:49,000
I know, but this is
mainly just a hobby for me.

351
00:15:49,083 --> 00:15:50,833
Then I'll gladly accept your kindness.

352
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:52,125
No, you won't.

353
00:15:52,208 --> 00:15:56,041
I will… look after your share
until we decide.

354
00:15:56,125 --> 00:15:57,375
Yeah. Whatever.

355
00:15:57,458 --> 00:15:59,833
Let's split it like this.

356
00:15:59,916 --> 00:16:04,083
Until now, I've done all the filming,
content, editing and directing.

357
00:16:04,958 --> 00:16:06,041
That's worth 90.

358
00:16:07,041 --> 00:16:08,208
And you get ten.

359
00:16:08,291 --> 00:16:09,166
What?

360
00:16:10,375 --> 00:16:12,833
Okay, then. Let's shake on it.

361
00:16:19,791 --> 00:16:20,875
[music stops]

362
00:16:20,958 --> 00:16:22,208
- Get real.
- Huh?

363
00:16:22,291 --> 00:16:25,666
Why is it 90/10?
I earn more than that making french fries.

364
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:27,458
Oh, oh, okay then.

365
00:16:27,541 --> 00:16:28,958
How about…

366
00:16:29,041 --> 00:16:31,416
I take 60 and you take 40?

367
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:34,833
<i>You </i>go get beaten up. See how <i>you </i>like it.

368
00:16:35,333 --> 00:16:36,791
Hey, hold on!

369
00:16:36,875 --> 00:16:38,083
Okay, you get 60.

370
00:16:38,791 --> 00:16:40,000
Seventy, then!

371
00:16:40,625 --> 00:16:42,083
Oh, what the hell?

372
00:16:42,166 --> 00:16:43,500
Eighty percent?

373
00:16:44,958 --> 00:16:46,833
All right, 90?

374
00:16:51,000 --> 00:16:53,291
Shall we start our next strategy session?

375
00:16:54,083 --> 00:16:56,416
I like to… please.

376
00:16:56,500 --> 00:17:00,291
[Shimura laughing]

377
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:02,500
- [Shimura squeals, laughs]
- [Toru] Get off!

378
00:17:04,916 --> 00:17:08,750
- [camera clicking]
- [pop music playing over speakers]

379
00:17:11,916 --> 00:17:12,750
TOO PRETTY!

380
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:13,916
SHE'S EYE CANDY

381
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,166
YUM YUM!

382
00:17:16,791 --> 00:17:18,375
[girls chatting]

383
00:17:18,458 --> 00:17:19,916
IT'S HAMAKEN'S GIRL LOL

384
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,750
GOOD TIME FOR 10,000 YEN?

385
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:23,541
SUCH A PICK-ME GIRL

386
00:17:23,625 --> 00:17:25,750
FOLLOWERS: 21,000

387
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:26,750
[tuts]

388
00:17:26,833 --> 00:17:28,833
[somber music playing]

389
00:17:32,500 --> 00:17:34,625
<i>VIRAL HIT</i>
SUBSCRIBERS: 102,000

390
00:17:37,166 --> 00:17:38,041
[sighs]

391
00:17:38,541 --> 00:17:40,041
[Hamaken growls]

392
00:17:41,083 --> 00:17:44,208
[growling]

393
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,833
[growling intensifies]/

394
00:17:51,125 --> 00:17:52,708
[music fades]

395
00:17:53,541 --> 00:17:54,750
[inhales sharply]

396
00:18:12,541 --> 00:18:15,291
Here's your change of clothes here.
I'll leave them here.

397
00:18:16,166 --> 00:18:17,916
Something good happened today?

398
00:18:18,416 --> 00:18:19,750
Why do you ask?

399
00:18:20,333 --> 00:18:22,666
You seem to be a happy fellow.

400
00:18:22,750 --> 00:18:24,625
No. Nothing in particular.

401
00:18:25,708 --> 00:18:30,125
I forgot. Is there
anything at all that you would like?

402
00:18:30,750 --> 00:18:32,791
Oh! Goodness. What do you mean?

403
00:18:33,291 --> 00:18:34,375
Mm.

404
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,625
There's nothing I want.

405
00:18:37,875 --> 00:18:40,625
Spend your money
only on something for yourself.

406
00:18:41,625 --> 00:18:43,666
It's your hard-earned money.

407
00:18:47,125 --> 00:18:49,375
[woman 1] Here. I bought you this new top.

408
00:18:49,458 --> 00:18:51,583
Oh, is this for me?

409
00:18:51,666 --> 00:18:54,000
- How pretty. [chuckles]
- [woman 2] You think so?

410
00:18:54,083 --> 00:18:55,958
- Oh. Thank you.
- [woman 1] Perfect.

411
00:18:56,041 --> 00:18:57,041
[woman 2 chuckles]

412
00:18:57,125 --> 00:18:58,500
- [laughs]
- [woman 1] I love it.

413
00:18:58,583 --> 00:19:00,083
- Looks great on you.
- [woman 2] Really?

414
00:19:00,166 --> 00:19:01,416
- Yes!
- [woman 2] Thank you.

415
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,541
[birds twittering]

416
00:19:03,625 --> 00:19:05,625
[Shimura inhales]

417
00:19:06,166 --> 00:19:07,875
Mm.

418
00:19:10,041 --> 00:19:10,875
CASHMERE

419
00:19:10,958 --> 00:19:12,208
Ah! It costs a fortune!

420
00:19:12,291 --> 00:19:14,708
- Why's it so expensive?
- [train alert blaring]

421
00:19:14,791 --> 00:19:15,833
[phone chimes]

422
00:19:17,750 --> 00:19:19,541
[approaching train clacking]

423
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:21,000
That's ridiculous.

424
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,083
[alert stops blaring]

425
00:19:28,041 --> 00:19:32,000
Okay, get your act together.
How am I gonna do this?

426
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:33,916
[Kaho] Shimura!

427
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,291
[exhales]

428
00:19:35,375 --> 00:19:36,416
[whimsical music playing]

429
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:39,041
[Shimura] <i>Here comes </i>True Beauty<i>.</i>

430
00:19:41,708 --> 00:19:43,625
Oh. Hi there.

431
00:19:43,708 --> 00:19:46,500
Sorry for the late notice.
Have you been waiting long?

432
00:19:46,583 --> 00:19:47,708
Not at all.

433
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:49,958
What's wrong? Are you feeling sick?

434
00:19:50,041 --> 00:19:51,250
No. No, I…

435
00:19:51,750 --> 00:19:53,250
On the contrary, I feel great.

436
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:54,416
[giggles]

437
00:19:54,500 --> 00:19:55,833
That's good. Okay.

438
00:19:55,916 --> 00:19:56,750
Mm.

439
00:19:57,541 --> 00:19:58,875
<i>Am I dreaming?</i>

440
00:19:59,375 --> 00:20:00,958
<i>It's just the two of us.</i>

441
00:20:03,625 --> 00:20:04,750
[Kaho laughs]

442
00:20:05,958 --> 00:20:07,750
Please let me know
when you're ready to order.

443
00:20:07,833 --> 00:20:09,166
[Kaho] Thank you very much.

444
00:20:09,666 --> 00:20:11,375
- [sighs]
- [pop music playing over speakers]

445
00:20:11,458 --> 00:20:13,625
I've been wanting to come here. It's nice.

446
00:20:13,708 --> 00:20:14,708
Yes, it is.

447
00:20:15,208 --> 00:20:17,083
I like the café scene a lot too.

448
00:20:17,166 --> 00:20:18,500
Oh, you do?

449
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,583
Oh, I'm so glad.

450
00:20:21,375 --> 00:20:23,625
Thank you for… the other day.

451
00:20:24,125 --> 00:20:28,000
This is my first part-time job,
so I was a bit lost.

452
00:20:28,083 --> 00:20:30,833
And I was very happy
when you intervened.

453
00:20:31,333 --> 00:20:32,416
So, I thank you.

454
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:33,333
Oh. [chuckles]

455
00:20:33,416 --> 00:20:35,166
You really don't have to.

456
00:20:36,208 --> 00:20:39,875
They got carried away.
Next time, I'll… tell them off.

457
00:20:39,958 --> 00:20:41,041
[laughs]

458
00:20:41,125 --> 00:20:42,791
- Oh, shall we order?
- Mm.

459
00:20:43,916 --> 00:20:45,375
Let's see. Mm.

460
00:20:46,083 --> 00:20:49,750
<i>What the hell?</i>
<i>800 yen for a cup of coffee?</i>

461
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:52,208
I think I'll have the strawberry parfait.

462
00:20:52,291 --> 00:20:55,500
[Shimura] <i>1,800 yen?</i>
<i>It's just strawberries and ice cream!</i>

463
00:20:55,583 --> 00:20:59,125
<i>Why does it cost so much?</i>
<i>That's my food budget for a whole week.</i>

464
00:20:59,708 --> 00:21:01,375
Uh, excuse me. Can we order?

465
00:21:01,458 --> 00:21:03,041
- [sever] Oh, sure.
- Thanks.

466
00:21:03,125 --> 00:21:05,791
- Uh, I'll have coffee.
- [server] One coffee.

467
00:21:05,875 --> 00:21:08,125
[Shimura] <i>One coffee costs</i>
<i>what I eat in three days.</i>

468
00:21:08,208 --> 00:21:11,333
- [server] One strawberry parfait.
- Okay. This is a good spot here.

469
00:21:11,833 --> 00:21:13,750
[Aki] We're invading his privacy.

470
00:21:13,833 --> 00:21:17,375
[Toru] Nonsense. If we just stream fights,
viewers will get bored.

471
00:21:18,375 --> 00:21:20,958
<i>Viral Hit</i>, starting live stream now.

472
00:21:21,041 --> 00:21:22,708
[pop music continues]

473
00:21:22,791 --> 00:21:24,166
SHIMURA'S ON A DATE LOL

474
00:21:24,250 --> 00:21:25,791
YOU GOT THIS, WALLFLOWER!

475
00:21:40,291 --> 00:21:41,958
[Kaho] Digging in.

476
00:21:44,875 --> 00:21:49,416
Uh, so, what made you want to work
at that burger joint?

477
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:50,958
Huh? What do you mean?

478
00:21:51,041 --> 00:21:54,750
I, uh, mean that,
you look like your family's well-to-do.

479
00:21:54,833 --> 00:21:58,583
[gasps] Uh, no. Not at all.
Really. We're just… normal.

480
00:21:58,666 --> 00:22:00,208
Ah, I see.

481
00:22:01,166 --> 00:22:04,041
[Shimura] <i>Oh no.</i>
<i>This is an awkward silence.</i>

482
00:22:05,208 --> 00:22:08,166
- Why is a hottie like her--
- She could be scamming him.

483
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:09,541
Gotta be.

484
00:22:09,625 --> 00:22:10,625
[men laughing]

485
00:22:10,708 --> 00:22:12,541
[man 1] Must be, surely.

486
00:22:12,625 --> 00:22:15,208
Doesn't this feel like
we're on a double date?

487
00:22:15,958 --> 00:22:18,166
- Want a bite of this?
- I don't like chicken.

488
00:22:18,250 --> 00:22:19,708
Oh, it's so tasty.

489
00:22:19,791 --> 00:22:22,166
And I don't like
watching people eat it either.

490
00:22:25,166 --> 00:22:27,708
He's dressed like… such a loser.

491
00:22:27,791 --> 00:22:30,833
Keep it down.
She can hear what you're saying.

492
00:22:31,375 --> 00:22:34,333
[Shimura] <i>Been listening to these guys</i>
<i>talking about us the whole time.</i>

493
00:22:34,416 --> 00:22:36,041
<i>I can hardly blame them.</i>

494
00:22:36,833 --> 00:22:38,750
<i>"Why would someone like her..." </i>

495
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:42,541
What's wrong?

496
00:22:43,791 --> 00:22:44,666
[groans] Whoa!

497
00:22:44,750 --> 00:22:46,500
- [man 2] Are you okay?
- What's wrong with her?

498
00:22:46,583 --> 00:22:48,083
[Toru] She must really hate chicken.

499
00:22:48,166 --> 00:22:49,625
Ah, jeez

500
00:22:52,333 --> 00:22:53,833
Aki, I'm sorry!

501
00:22:53,916 --> 00:22:56,541
I… didn't realize
you hated chicken that much.

502
00:22:56,625 --> 00:22:57,833
This

503
00:22:58,375 --> 00:22:59,833
is in bad taste.

504
00:23:00,333 --> 00:23:01,416
[whimpers]

505
00:23:05,708 --> 00:23:09,416
[laid-back music playing
softly over speakers]

506
00:23:10,125 --> 00:23:12,416
[indistinct chatter]

507
00:23:15,625 --> 00:23:18,000
I'm sorry… about today.

508
00:23:18,625 --> 00:23:20,416
I shouldn't have dragged you here.

509
00:23:20,916 --> 00:23:21,750
Huh?

510
00:23:22,333 --> 00:23:23,791
Let me get this. [chuckles]

511
00:23:24,708 --> 00:23:25,708
[Shimura sighs]

512
00:23:26,791 --> 00:23:28,458
You've got it all wrong.

513
00:23:28,541 --> 00:23:30,750
I thought that

514
00:23:31,250 --> 00:23:35,541
you were embarrassed
to be seen out with me.

515
00:23:37,458 --> 00:23:40,416
Besides, I… um, well,

516
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:43,958
I've never hung out
one-on-one with a girl.

517
00:23:44,458 --> 00:23:48,416
And I've never actually…
been to a fancy café.

518
00:23:51,000 --> 00:23:52,125
[gentle music playing]

519
00:23:52,208 --> 00:23:54,875
I, uh, don't really know
what to talk about

520
00:23:54,958 --> 00:23:58,041
or… or what to say to a girl.

521
00:23:58,541 --> 00:23:59,708
And I…

522
00:24:01,791 --> 00:24:03,041
I'm sorry.

523
00:24:05,958 --> 00:24:07,083
Wanna go outside?

524
00:24:08,458 --> 00:24:09,333
Huh?

525
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:13,375
It's a nice day. Let's talk outside.

526
00:24:16,625 --> 00:24:17,708
Mm.

527
00:24:17,791 --> 00:24:19,166
[cooing]

528
00:24:20,791 --> 00:24:23,750
Oh, really? Yeah, sure.

529
00:24:24,583 --> 00:24:26,125
- Uh, sorry.
- Mm.

530
00:24:26,208 --> 00:24:27,541
That was a friend.

531
00:24:28,916 --> 00:24:31,708
- Ah.
- Actually, he's at the same school as you.

532
00:24:31,791 --> 00:24:32,958
Oh. Who is it?

533
00:24:33,041 --> 00:24:34,625
Ogi Tatsuya. Know him?

534
00:24:35,708 --> 00:24:37,000
Ogi… yeah.

535
00:24:37,916 --> 00:24:38,750
[whispers] Him?

536
00:24:41,250 --> 00:24:43,791
Yes. Of course, I know him.

537
00:24:43,875 --> 00:24:46,750
We're… we're like… besties.

538
00:24:46,833 --> 00:24:48,208
- Ah! Really?
- Yeah.

539
00:24:48,291 --> 00:24:50,375
He says he's just around the corner.

540
00:24:50,458 --> 00:24:51,916
Oh. Is that right?

541
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:54,375
He wants to say hi.

542
00:24:54,458 --> 00:24:57,500
Uh, no, today is a bit… yeah. Oh yeah.

543
00:24:57,583 --> 00:24:58,791
- I, uh--
- [Ogi] Asamiya!

544
00:24:58,875 --> 00:24:59,750
[Kaho] Ogi!

545
00:25:00,250 --> 00:25:02,541
- So you really were close by.
- [Ogi] Yep.

546
00:25:03,208 --> 00:25:05,125
Ah! You know Shimura.

547
00:25:05,208 --> 00:25:07,208
He said you two were friends.

548
00:25:07,291 --> 00:25:08,416
Friends?

549
00:25:09,458 --> 00:25:10,791
Me and him?

550
00:25:17,666 --> 00:25:18,791
Well, sure we are.

551
00:25:19,666 --> 00:25:21,291
- We're at the same school.
- Huh?

552
00:25:22,250 --> 00:25:24,583
You just started live streaming,
didn't you?

553
00:25:24,666 --> 00:25:27,958
- Oh. Did you?
- Ah. Just a little, yeah.

554
00:25:28,041 --> 00:25:31,000
- [Kota] Ah.
- I like your channel, <i>Viral Hit</i>.

555
00:25:31,666 --> 00:25:33,083
Oh, thank you.

556
00:25:33,583 --> 00:25:37,583
- You know, you're… stronger than you look.
- Huh?

557
00:25:37,666 --> 00:25:40,250
You took the hit
before your opponent could swing.

558
00:25:40,333 --> 00:25:42,041
That way, it's less damage done to you.

559
00:25:43,875 --> 00:25:46,791
- Mm.
- I'm guessing it hurts less that way.

560
00:25:47,708 --> 00:25:48,791
[Shimura] <i>Ogi.</i>

561
00:25:49,916 --> 00:25:52,666
<i>He might know something</i>
<i>about that chicken guy.</i>

562
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:59,541
Hey, wanna go for a walk?
It's nice over there.

563
00:25:59,625 --> 00:26:00,500
Sure.

564
00:26:08,541 --> 00:26:11,916
There's a rival here now!
This is interesting!

565
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:14,750
Stay tuned. You don't wanna miss this!

566
00:26:14,833 --> 00:26:16,958
- [Kaho laughing]
- [Ogi] Asamiya, wait up!

567
00:26:17,500 --> 00:26:18,500
[Kaho sighs] Oh.

568
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,125
Remember this?

569
00:26:20,208 --> 00:26:22,166
- [Ogi] Yeah. Course I do.
- [Kaho laughs]

570
00:26:22,875 --> 00:26:25,833
- [Ogi] We took the ferry.
- Yeah, we did.  I'd love to do that again.

571
00:26:25,916 --> 00:26:27,791
- Do you think we could?
- [Ogi] Yeah, sure we can.

572
00:26:27,875 --> 00:26:29,333
[Kaho laughs] Yeah.

573
00:26:29,833 --> 00:26:31,875
[poignant music playing]

574
00:26:36,208 --> 00:26:37,625
Is your gym close by?

575
00:26:37,708 --> 00:26:39,083
Yeah. It's really close.

576
00:26:39,166 --> 00:26:41,000
Ah. I didn't know.

577
00:26:41,083 --> 00:26:42,416
- [Shimura] <i>Question.</i>
<i>- </i>[Ogi] <i>I mean…</i>

578
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:46,166
[Shimura] <i>Choose the couple that looks</i>
<i>the best together from the options below.</i>

579
00:26:46,250 --> 00:26:49,625
<i>A question so easy,</i>
<i>even grade school kids can solve.</i>

580
00:26:50,125 --> 00:26:51,875
<i>I know the answer myself.</i>

581
00:26:52,625 --> 00:26:53,833
<i>The answer is simple.</i>

582
00:26:53,916 --> 00:26:55,166
[Kaho] Yeah, I'd be interested.

583
00:26:55,250 --> 00:26:56,291
<i>The third wheel…</i>

584
00:26:56,375 --> 00:26:57,250
[Kaho] Really?

585
00:26:57,333 --> 00:26:58,916
<i>- …is me.</i>
<i>- </i>[Ogi] No, you're not.

586
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:00,458
[Kaho] I am. I mean it.

587
00:27:01,333 --> 00:27:02,208
Uh, sorry.

588
00:27:02,291 --> 00:27:03,875
[poignant music continues]

589
00:27:04,666 --> 00:27:06,708
I'm sorry about this.

590
00:27:08,291 --> 00:27:11,166
My ingrown toenail hurts. I have to leave.

591
00:27:11,250 --> 00:27:12,208
[both] Ingrown toenail?

592
00:27:12,291 --> 00:27:14,791
Uh, yes, my toenail.

593
00:27:15,583 --> 00:27:16,625
See ya.

594
00:27:17,250 --> 00:27:19,250
Uh, hey, Shimura, wait.

595
00:27:19,333 --> 00:27:22,708
[Shimura] <i>If I stay here any longer,</i>
<i>I might die from self-loathing.</i>

596
00:27:25,208 --> 00:27:26,583
[Kaho] You think he's okay?

597
00:27:26,666 --> 00:27:28,250
- [Ogi] He'll be fine.
- [Kaho sighs]

598
00:27:35,083 --> 00:27:37,166
Uh! What's with you? Hey?

599
00:27:37,250 --> 00:27:38,541
Oh! You knew?

600
00:27:38,625 --> 00:27:39,666
You're so obvious!

601
00:27:39,750 --> 00:27:41,041
Oh, when did you catch on?

602
00:27:41,125 --> 00:27:42,458
Since you were at the café.

603
00:27:42,541 --> 00:27:44,416
[groans] Ah, seriously?

604
00:27:45,291 --> 00:27:46,791
I just have to ask…

605
00:27:48,083 --> 00:27:49,250
That you're not streaming now?

606
00:27:49,333 --> 00:27:53,166
Of course not.
Privacy's important, isn't it?

607
00:27:54,541 --> 00:27:55,750
[Shimura grunting]

608
00:27:55,833 --> 00:27:56,916
Hey! Give it back!

609
00:27:57,000 --> 00:27:57,958
BUSTED LOL
HILARIOUS

610
00:27:58,041 --> 00:27:59,125
Give it to me!

611
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:01,791
Why the hell would you stream it?!

612
00:28:01,875 --> 00:28:04,208
I thought it was a good way
to shake things up.

613
00:28:04,291 --> 00:28:07,541
- This is the worst!
- Yeah, I agree.

614
00:28:07,625 --> 00:28:09,125
Yeah. <i>You </i>are the worst. All right?

615
00:28:09,208 --> 00:28:11,416
Ingrown toenail? That was so lame!

616
00:28:11,500 --> 00:28:13,125
It was all that I could think of.

617
00:28:13,208 --> 00:28:16,500
Not that! I'm saying you ran away
like a scared little chicken!

618
00:28:16,583 --> 00:28:19,750
- What else was I supposed to do?
- [Toru sighs]

619
00:28:22,625 --> 00:28:25,791
Love, it's like a game we play.

620
00:28:26,291 --> 00:28:27,125
Huh?

621
00:28:27,208 --> 00:28:30,416
And a lovely woman is
the prize you get for playing.

622
00:28:31,166 --> 00:28:34,875
If a tough contender comes along,
are you just gonna throw in the towel?

623
00:28:35,708 --> 00:28:38,541
It's okay with me.
If I don't fight, I don't lose.

624
00:28:39,708 --> 00:28:41,833
You coward! You're a loser!

625
00:28:41,916 --> 00:28:44,291
- Listen closely!
- [poignant music playing]

626
00:28:44,375 --> 00:28:48,166
A world-famous basketballer
once said these words,

627
00:28:48,250 --> 00:28:51,166
"When you give up,
that's when the game ends." You get it?

628
00:28:52,875 --> 00:28:56,458
Are you seriously giving up here?

629
00:28:56,541 --> 00:28:59,375
Who was it that got back up
when Hamaken knocked you down?

630
00:28:59,458 --> 00:29:02,416
Who stood up to that other thug
'cause her contact was on your phone?

631
00:29:02,500 --> 00:29:06,000
The buzzer hasn't sounded yet!
The match isn't over!

632
00:29:06,083 --> 00:29:08,333
Go! You've gotta get her back!

633
00:29:10,583 --> 00:29:11,625
Kaneko.

634
00:29:13,166 --> 00:29:14,250
You've…

635
00:29:16,916 --> 00:29:18,208
[yelps] Ah!

636
00:29:18,291 --> 00:29:21,500
Thank you! Thank you!
You've helped me come to my senses!

637
00:29:21,583 --> 00:29:23,875
Stop it! We're friends, aren't we?

638
00:29:23,958 --> 00:29:25,291
[panting]

639
00:29:25,375 --> 00:29:26,375
[sniffles]

640
00:29:26,875 --> 00:29:28,166
I'll do it!

641
00:29:30,083 --> 00:29:32,416
That's right. I'm proud of myself.

642
00:29:32,500 --> 00:29:35,166
A true streamer! [laughs]

643
00:29:35,250 --> 00:29:36,333
Okay, here we go.

644
00:29:36,416 --> 00:29:38,583
"Confessing to a girl
who's out of my league

645
00:29:38,666 --> 00:29:40,791
and then ready to get rejected." Whoo!

646
00:29:40,875 --> 00:29:43,791
[laughing]

647
00:29:47,750 --> 00:29:49,291
Asamiya!

648
00:29:50,666 --> 00:29:51,541
Oh!

649
00:29:52,541 --> 00:29:53,416
[chuckles]

650
00:29:55,583 --> 00:29:58,375
There's still something
I, I wanted to talk to you about.

651
00:29:58,458 --> 00:29:59,958
- Uh, talk?
- Yeah, yeah.

652
00:30:01,250 --> 00:30:04,333
- Where's Ogi?
- He has practice. He went to his gym.

653
00:30:04,416 --> 00:30:06,000
Oh. I see.

654
00:30:06,083 --> 00:30:07,416
[both chuckle]

655
00:30:07,500 --> 00:30:09,291
How's your toenail?

656
00:30:09,375 --> 00:30:11,750
- Oh, yeah, it's fine. All good now.
- [chuckles]

657
00:30:11,833 --> 00:30:14,416
I see. So, what did you want to say?

658
00:30:14,500 --> 00:30:17,791
Oh, yes, well, I… I, um…

659
00:30:18,583 --> 00:30:20,958
I wanted to ask, what is your ideal type?

660
00:30:21,541 --> 00:30:23,583
[laughs] That's a bit out of the blue.

661
00:30:23,666 --> 00:30:27,166
Sorry, I, I wanted to ask you that.

662
00:30:27,791 --> 00:30:30,541
Mm… someone strong, I think.

663
00:30:31,125 --> 00:30:33,875
- Someone strong?
- What about you? What type do you like?

664
00:30:33,958 --> 00:30:35,375
Huh? Oh, me?

665
00:30:35,458 --> 00:30:38,250
Uh, I like, um… I like…

666
00:30:38,833 --> 00:30:41,125
<i>Someone like you, Asamiya.</i>

667
00:30:41,625 --> 00:30:44,416
<i>No. There's no way</i>
<i>I could actually say that.</i>

668
00:30:47,291 --> 00:30:49,750
I just knew you were filming me.

669
00:30:49,833 --> 00:30:51,416
Knock it off, will ya?

670
00:30:51,916 --> 00:30:54,291
Kanegon, what happened to your face?

671
00:30:54,958 --> 00:30:56,000
Run…

672
00:30:56,083 --> 00:30:57,208
- [dull thud]
- [grunts]

673
00:30:57,791 --> 00:30:58,791
[Shimura] Huh.

674
00:30:59,250 --> 00:31:01,541
- [tense music playing]
- Thanks very much, Kanegon.

675
00:31:01,625 --> 00:31:04,958
Luckily, your broadcast saved me
the trouble of finding you.

676
00:31:05,666 --> 00:31:06,791
Sure did.

677
00:31:07,416 --> 00:31:10,166
Didn't I tell you that I'd make you pay?

678
00:31:10,250 --> 00:31:11,708
What do you think you're doing?

679
00:31:11,791 --> 00:31:13,708
- I'm calling the police--
- Asamiya.

680
00:31:14,208 --> 00:31:15,541
You… go on ahead.

681
00:31:15,625 --> 00:31:16,541
[Hamaken] Say what?

682
00:31:17,458 --> 00:31:18,291
Go?

683
00:31:19,333 --> 00:31:22,000
- [Kaho gasps]
- You're not going anywhere.

684
00:31:22,083 --> 00:31:24,041
Let go of me! [whimpers]

685
00:31:24,125 --> 00:31:25,333
[Hamaken] You! Get here!

686
00:31:25,416 --> 00:31:26,333
Asamiya!

687
00:31:26,416 --> 00:31:28,166
- Let me go!
- [Hamaken] Huh?

688
00:31:28,250 --> 00:31:32,125
You acted like you weren't interested
in men when I tried to get your number.

689
00:31:32,208 --> 00:31:34,208
- Huh? You bitch.
- [whimpering]

690
00:31:34,291 --> 00:31:35,708
[Kaho] Stop this!

691
00:31:35,791 --> 00:31:37,291
[Shimura] <i>I must stay calm.</i>

692
00:31:37,375 --> 00:31:39,583
<i>I can't lose my cool before he does.</i>

693
00:31:39,666 --> 00:31:42,500
[TOU-KEI] <i>It's easy to defeat someone</i>
<i>who's lost his cool.</i>

694
00:31:42,833 --> 00:31:46,125
- [Kaho cries] Stop it! Leave me alone!
<i>- I have to restrain myself.</i>

695
00:31:46,208 --> 00:31:47,916
- [Kaho] I said stop!
- Hamaken!

696
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:48,833
[gasps]

697
00:31:51,125 --> 00:31:53,458
You only fight girls, do you?

698
00:31:53,541 --> 00:31:55,666
[Shimura] <i>That's right. Get him worked up.</i>

699
00:31:56,708 --> 00:31:58,291
- Okay.
- [groans]

700
00:31:58,375 --> 00:31:59,333
Shimura…

701
00:32:00,708 --> 00:32:02,083
Bastard.

702
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:04,708
You bastard! You're toast!

703
00:32:04,791 --> 00:32:06,875
[Shimura] <i>I can do it. I'll use that move.</i>

704
00:32:07,375 --> 00:32:10,583
- [grunting]
- [Shimura grunts]

705
00:32:15,666 --> 00:32:16,583
What?

706
00:32:16,666 --> 00:32:17,541
[Hamaken] Dumbass.

707
00:32:17,625 --> 00:32:19,958
You think I didn't watch
your video, did you?

708
00:32:20,041 --> 00:32:22,083
You upload everything online.

709
00:32:22,166 --> 00:32:24,416
[Shimura] <i>Ouch. This hurts really bad.</i>

710
00:32:24,500 --> 00:32:25,541
Shimura!

711
00:32:27,250 --> 00:32:30,666
<i>- What should I do? What should I do now?</i>
- [thunder rumbles]

712
00:32:30,750 --> 00:32:31,916
[rain pattering]

713
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:35,750
<i>My mind, it's gone blank.</i>

714
00:32:36,500 --> 00:32:39,416
[moaning]

715
00:32:40,583 --> 00:32:42,291
[somber music playing]

716
00:32:43,041 --> 00:32:45,000
[Shimura] <i>My house sits in the shadows,</i>

717
00:32:46,750 --> 00:32:49,583
<i>way below the towering skyscrapers.</i>

718
00:32:49,666 --> 00:32:53,708
- The Argentine Backbreaker!
- [students cheering]

719
00:32:53,791 --> 00:32:55,500
[student voices fade]

720
00:32:55,583 --> 00:32:57,708
[Shimura] <i>Perhaps that's the reason…</i>

721
00:32:58,625 --> 00:33:03,375
<i>the reason why…</i>
<i>I've spent my life in the shadows.</i>

722
00:33:04,875 --> 00:33:08,625
<i>But then, this once-in-a-lifetime</i>
<i>opportunity came to me.</i>

723
00:33:08,708 --> 00:33:10,916
[gentle music playing]

724
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:15,000
<i>I thought I could finally be an ordinary</i>
<i>high school student like everybody else.</i>

725
00:33:17,250 --> 00:33:19,541
<i>But I was a fool to dream</i>
<i>that could happen.</i>

726
00:33:20,750 --> 00:33:22,833
[grunting]

727
00:33:22,916 --> 00:33:26,458
[Shimura] <i>And so now…</i>
<i>I'm paying the price.</i>

728
00:33:28,583 --> 00:33:29,833
<i>And here I am,</i>

729
00:33:31,500 --> 00:33:33,375
<i>back to being a loser again.</i>

730
00:33:33,875 --> 00:33:35,666
[echoing] Shimura!

731
00:33:40,666 --> 00:33:42,708
- I'm home.
- You're home early.

732
00:33:42,791 --> 00:33:44,458
Not out with your friends today?

733
00:33:45,416 --> 00:33:46,708
[Aki] He's got bad taste.

734
00:33:46,791 --> 00:33:47,750
Huh?

735
00:33:48,250 --> 00:33:50,250
[gentle music continues]

736
00:33:52,750 --> 00:33:53,875
THE STREAM HAS ENDED

737
00:33:53,958 --> 00:33:55,583
[Aki] Did he finally stop streaming?

738
00:33:57,791 --> 00:34:02,250
WATCH WHAT HAPPENS NEXT ON HAMAKEN TV

739
00:34:08,166 --> 00:34:11,000
[Kaho] <i>Shimura! Shimura! Please! No more!</i>

740
00:34:11,083 --> 00:34:13,000
[Shimura] <i>I always thought</i>

741
00:34:13,083 --> 00:34:16,166
<i>that it was better to get hit</i>
<i>than to fight back.</i>

742
00:34:16,250 --> 00:34:17,375
[gasping]

743
00:34:17,458 --> 00:34:18,500
Hey!

744
00:34:19,208 --> 00:34:20,666
I'm not finished with you.

745
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:24,666
[strained] Please, let her go.

746
00:34:24,750 --> 00:34:25,583
What?

747
00:34:28,166 --> 00:34:29,916
Please let her go.

748
00:34:33,625 --> 00:34:37,583
Let Asamiya go home.
Please. Please let her go.

749
00:34:37,666 --> 00:34:39,333
Let me go. Shimura!

750
00:34:39,416 --> 00:34:43,875
[Shimura] <i>I don't want her to see</i>
<i>my pathetic self any longer.</i>

751
00:34:44,458 --> 00:34:47,791
What are you trying to show off for? Huh?

752
00:34:47,875 --> 00:34:49,791
You're nothing but a loser, Shimura!

753
00:34:50,375 --> 00:34:51,500
Shimura!

754
00:34:51,583 --> 00:34:55,875
[Shimura] <i>Asamiya was the one person</i>
<i>who I didn't want to see</i>

755
00:34:55,958 --> 00:34:58,708
<i>just how weak and pathetic I really am.</i>

756
00:35:01,458 --> 00:35:04,416
[rain pouring on live stream]

757
00:35:07,458 --> 00:35:08,583
[shudders]

758
00:35:13,500 --> 00:35:15,500
Please forgive me.

759
00:35:17,041 --> 00:35:18,583
[Hamaken] Shimura.

760
00:35:19,666 --> 00:35:20,791
[groans]

761
00:35:20,875 --> 00:35:21,708
That won't do.

762
00:35:22,708 --> 00:35:24,833
Strip and apologize

763
00:35:25,916 --> 00:35:27,583
to the viewers there.

764
00:35:28,416 --> 00:35:30,416
[somber music playing]

765
00:35:31,500 --> 00:35:34,083
Have you got any idea
how many viewers are tuned in

766
00:35:34,166 --> 00:35:36,208
and looking at this now? Huh?!

767
00:35:37,250 --> 00:35:40,041
[Toru crying] Shimura, I'm sorry.

768
00:35:40,125 --> 00:35:43,333
I said that I didn't want to do this.

769
00:35:46,541 --> 00:35:47,791
NO NEED TO APOLOGIZE

770
00:35:47,875 --> 00:35:48,916
SHIMURA!

771
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:50,041
PLEASE STOP

772
00:35:50,125 --> 00:35:51,208
[Hamaken laughing]

773
00:35:51,291 --> 00:35:53,000
<i>You're doing great camera work.</i>

774
00:35:53,083 --> 00:35:54,458
He's such a loser.

775
00:35:54,541 --> 00:35:55,875
[Hamaken and boy laughing]

776
00:35:56,625 --> 00:35:57,625
[Toru groans]

777
00:35:58,125 --> 00:36:01,375
You're very good at it.
At the camera work. I'll give you that.

778
00:36:01,458 --> 00:36:02,750
[laughing]

779
00:36:02,833 --> 00:36:04,500
[Shimura sighs deeply]

780
00:36:05,666 --> 00:36:07,875
[Hamaken] Now, hurry up and strip.

781
00:36:08,458 --> 00:36:09,875
If you do, I'll let her go.

782
00:36:09,958 --> 00:36:10,833
[boy] Strip!

783
00:36:11,833 --> 00:36:14,041
[Hamaken laughing]

784
00:36:17,666 --> 00:36:18,750
Hey!

785
00:36:20,166 --> 00:36:21,208
[grunts]

786
00:36:21,291 --> 00:36:22,333
Enough is enough!

787
00:36:24,333 --> 00:36:28,083
[Shimura] <i>The girl I'm in love with…</i>
<i>showed more courage than I did.</i>

788
00:36:28,166 --> 00:36:30,541
- Hey! Don't touch him! Shut up, bitch!
- Let go! Let go!

789
00:36:30,625 --> 00:36:33,791
[Shimura] <i>And all my life,</i>
<i>I've never felt so pathetic.</i>

790
00:36:33,875 --> 00:36:35,208
- [Kaho wails]
- [Shimura] Hamaken!

791
00:36:35,291 --> 00:36:36,208
[Hamaken] Huh?

792
00:36:38,500 --> 00:36:41,583
- [belt jangling]
- [boy laughing]

793
00:36:42,583 --> 00:36:44,208
[Hamaken and boy laughing]

794
00:36:45,500 --> 00:36:47,458
[Shimura] <i>I've failed as a man.</i>

795
00:36:48,291 --> 00:36:50,333
I've stripped. Are you happy?

796
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:52,958
- [Hamaken laughing] Oh!
- Now let her go.

797
00:36:53,041 --> 00:36:54,791
[both laughing]

798
00:36:54,875 --> 00:36:56,916
[boy] He did it! Stripped it all off!

799
00:36:57,000 --> 00:36:59,000
[both laughing uproariously]

800
00:36:59,708 --> 00:37:01,250
[Hamaken] <i>Get this on camera!</i>

801
00:37:01,333 --> 00:37:03,500
[boy] Keep rolling, man!

802
00:37:04,375 --> 00:37:06,208
[Shimura] <i>This will have to be it.</i>

803
00:37:06,291 --> 00:37:08,958
<i>I don't have the spine to win in a fight.</i>

804
00:37:10,041 --> 00:37:13,208
<i>So this is the only way</i>
<i>I can protect Asamiya.</i>

805
00:37:13,291 --> 00:37:16,125
[Hamaken laughing]

806
00:37:16,208 --> 00:37:17,166
[Shimura] <i>But I'll</i>

807
00:37:18,208 --> 00:37:20,291
<i>at least get in one hit.</i>

808
00:37:21,416 --> 00:37:22,500
<i>This is my…</i>

809
00:37:23,083 --> 00:37:24,500
- Huh?
- [boy] What?

810
00:37:24,583 --> 00:37:25,625
[Toru] Shimura?

811
00:37:25,708 --> 00:37:28,000
Hey. Stop that.

812
00:37:28,083 --> 00:37:29,416
- [boy] Hey!
- [Hamaken] Stop that.

813
00:37:29,500 --> 00:37:31,125
<i>- My last stand.</i>
- [boy] What are you doing?

814
00:37:31,208 --> 00:37:33,333
[Hamaken] Hey! You're gonna get us banned.

815
00:37:34,916 --> 00:37:35,958
Hey!

816
00:37:38,125 --> 00:37:39,625
Hey! Stop!

817
00:37:39,708 --> 00:37:42,000
[Shimura] <i>Goodbye, Asamiya.</i>

818
00:37:44,083 --> 00:37:46,750
[Japanese rock music playing]

819
00:37:55,916 --> 00:38:02,250
VIRAL HIT

820
00:38:08,125 --> 00:38:10,166
[Japanese rock music continues]

821
00:39:19,458 --> 00:39:20,458
[music ends]
